description.narrative:
Secretariat's capacity to prepare timely progress reports of NHRSAP is strengthened to a significant extent;
Actions Plans for 2016-2020 Prepared and Approved;
Level of Participation and monitoring of civil society in implementation of NHRS is higher by 50% compared to the beginning of the UN Joint Programme;
NHRS and its action plans are implemented with a due diligence as evidenced by reports of international organizations, PDO and civil society
Visibility of NHRS and AP in media, including social media is higher;
Judicial practice improved concerning permitting access to personal data  all judicial decisions on permitting access to personal data are justified and reasonable;
PDPI capacity strengthened to monitor implementation of personal data regulations by private and public sector;
Selected government agencies improve PDP in their activities
Awareness of PDPI office is higher
The oversight role of the parliament over human rights issues, with special emphasis on implementation of PDO and UN Human Rights Mechanisms recommendations strengthened to a significant extent and institutionalized in legal framework;
Human rights based approach is increasingly used in legislative activities and adopted legislation is in line with international human rights standards
Draft regulations on independent investigative body are developed;

comment.narrative:
The IACHR and Secretariat have insufficient analytical skills, low capacity to analyse inputs from civil society, to translate  from overall policies to sectorial/ministerial actions,  to report to the UN and other international human rights mechanisms.
Media, CSOs and officials at all level, including regional bodies, are not aware of NHRS and AP. 
PDPI's office is a newly established organization with limited resources and awareness
The oversight role of the Parliament over issues related to human rights is relatively low;
Capacity to use human rights based approach is low
Independent investigative body for crimes committed by law-enforcement officies  does not exist;
awareness on torture and ill treatment among relevant stakeholders is low;
NPM has low capacity to monitor penitentiary establishments in line with relevant international standards;

